🔥 Root Cause (very clear)

In agent-based installation:

👉 There is NO dedicated bootstrap node
👉 Bootstrap runs on one of the master nodes

So your command:

--bootstrap 72.2.0.17
--master 72.2.0.15 --master 72.2.0.13 --master 72.2.0.17

❌ Wrong usage (you treated bootstrap as separate)


---

✅ Correct Approach for Agent-Based

🧠 Key Concept

Bootstrap = runs on one of the masters

Usually the first master that started installation



---

✅ Step 1: Identify bootstrap node

From your masters:

Try SSH:

ssh core@72.2.0.13
ssh core@72.2.0.15
ssh core@72.2.0.17

Then check on each:

journalctl -b -u bootkube.service

👉 The node which shows logs = bootstrap node


---

✅ Step 2: Use correct gather command

Example:

openshift-install gather bootstrap \
  --bootstrap 72.2.0.13 \
  --master 72.2.0.13 \
  --master 72.2.0.15 \
  --master 72.2.0.17 \
  --key ~/.ssh/id_rsa


---

⚠️ Important fixes for your case

1. ❌ You didn’t provide SSH key earlier

Must include:

--key ~/.ssh/id_rsa


---

2. ❌ SSH user issue

Installer uses core user

Test:

